column9: Clearly articulated the 2025 initiatives; however, the measurable impact to the client was not fully clear. Strong overview, but additional quantification of outcomes would strengthen this area.
column11: Mentioned value-add activities, but lacked financial framing. To reach a higher score, value adds should be tied more clearly to cost avoidance or tangible impact. This is an opportunity to strengthen the approach in 2026.
column13: Demonstrated strong delivery of cost savings. Clear articulation of savings achieved and effectiveness of execution.
column15: Showed clear improvement and adaptability, including a strong pivot from Q2 to Q4. Innovation efforts and progress toward improving how we innovate for the client were evident.
column17: Completely transparent in addressing challenges. Clearly owned gaps and outlined corrective actions with supporting timelines. Strong accountability and leadership demonstrated.
column19: Clearly articulated a strong vision and roadmap for 2026. Strategy was well thought out and supported by clear planning, as evidenced in the presentation materials.
column21: Demonstrated strong role maturity and clarity in personal goals. Showed readiness for continued growth and leadership development.
column23: It was the first one -> good

column11: Value adds were broad but did not quantify the cost offset for the client.
column13: Delivered cost savings across all sites.
column15: Would have liked to see roadmap for executing the proposed innovations. What was done in 2025 on the innovation side?
column17: Reviewed challenges but would have wanted to see more specificity within the challenges. How can these issues be prevented in the future?
column19: Well established growth plan for 2026. 3 site bids upcoming. Specific path to securing these locations would have improved the overall delivery.
column21: How are you measuring success? Answer to Val’s question was well delivered but would have benefitted from being incorporated in the presentation.

column9: Some time constraints necessitated speed through this sections but I felt like end impact of projects could have been highlighted in more detail.
column11: Explanation and review of Value Adds and Cost avoidances was great but no summary of dollars impact. This was addressed on the call but lack of values hurts this section. There was a very short turnaround time but even estimates would have helped to contextualize the impact of the different activities.
column13: Very clear explanation of cost savings by location with cost breakdown included.
column15: Clear articulation of projects but was a little light on what the why of the project was. Would have been helpful to hear what problem the innovations were trying to solve.
column17: Between the opening section in 4I and the slide deck I felt this was covered very well. Issues were tackled head on without avoidance or deflection and clear remedies were articulated. Very good job answering questions in this section.
column19: Path forward was well done. There were clear targets/objectives and a real plan on how to achieve them.
column21: There were good goals in this section but all account focused not personal. I think some of this content could have been in the path forward and I would have liked to see at least one self-reflective goal.

column9: Clarity lacking. Attempted to include too much data about relationships and did not focus on clearly articulating the specific projects and initiatives.
column11: Value adds and cost avoidances were not clearly identified. There is opportunity to bring into this discussion some of the financial tracking that we currently provide to Merck Direct to show this data.
column13: Good job here. Include specific details and the cost savings drivers.
column15: OK job here.  Slight mention of Autonomous and could have expanded on outcomes and results. Failed to mention all autonomous being used (i.e. window cleaning) Good but long story on pest control. More high-level descriptions needed.
column17: MYO explanation good. Clearly articulated Merck reasoning. Failed to speak to what percentages and initiatives that we proposed based on the Merck ask and requirements for MYO.
column21: Personal goal to develop management team but needs to include more detail. Need to articulate better.
column23: Very hard to follow. Floated around and did not stick to topic which really impacted his messaging.

column9: Clearly outlined and articulate his 2025 timeline of what he provided to his accounts. Savings, innovations, etc. carried through all initiatives more than just one. Thought outside the box, utilize outside resources verse depending on corporate to push. Positive outcomes including renewals and growth!
column11: Provided his clients numerous value adds and cost avoidance. Brining the latest and greatest in his space. Has his clients numerous value bets interest at heart.
column13: Delivered cost savings which resulted in off market renewals.
column15: Demonstrated very well how Mark can continue to innovate, bringing ideas to the clients attention. He pushed the envelope to counties to test products, learned for each of them.
column17: Challenges while navigating JLL Serv, competing interest.

column9: Clearly framed the initiatives that were most impactful for LAM. Very clear you were able to create value, adding both revenue resources and benefits to the client. Outstanding!
column11: Your tracking of the true value is rare to see. Often time people struggle to articulate the benefit to the customer.
column13: Great job tracking and measuring this.
column15: You are able to tell your story well, both with equipment and processes.
column17: There was an opportunity to call out the actions needed to get closure of the challenges you have. I would focus on what you need from others and not just being accountable for the site level challenges but where leaders or others can support.
column19: I would have liked to have seen your actual plan around LAM transition and increase. How will you use the dollars whats the schedule and roll out for that increase.
column21: I would have liked to have understood your goals you have for yourself that aligns to the AD role. Love the smartsheet tracker and taking things in smaller bite size pieces making it documented.
column23: The material was well organized, the communication was well thought out. While the flow worked well for you I would have liked a tone that supported your drive to expand, or get everything you need to be the clients only choice.

column9: Love the way you thought of how to be exclusive as a provider! Great details on the projects and I was impressed that you captured the clients feedback and impressions.
column11: Clearly explained savings, value delivery and management of the team through challenging them. I appreciate the thinking behind this example thebgreen cleaning. Future state quantify the value add in 2026.
column15: Love that you thought outside of the box on innovation. While you were able to come with some thing I’d like you to dive deeper into innovation.
column17: Your challenges and opportunities slide is the best I have seen so far. Your clear explanation of how you overcame your challenges reassures me we have the right leadership in you!
column19: Timelines are critical to me. Make sure you hold yourself and team accountable to the commitments communicated here. Will be interesting to see your half year review.
column21: I am 100% aligned with your goals and thought process around what’s important.
column23: You lead discussion, drive transformation while being transparent and effective. Really appreciate the the thought put into these discussion.

column9: Great job of highlighting impact to the customer and strategic impact of all key projects. I was easily able to follow the details of the projects
column11: The explanation of what and how was very strong. There was quantified dollars to Cost Avoidance but not for the Value adds. Even if the exact dollar amount isn't known of tracked it would have been good to at least get a ball park amount to evaluate vs the other two categories.,
column13: Clearly articulated project value and numbers associated with the cost savings.
column15: Robotics is a good innovation and seems like an inevitability and is just a matter of time. I would consider succession planning to be an account goal and not and innovation. It is 100% a best practice!
column17: This section was very well done very clear ownership and what was being done to correct issues without making excuses.
column19: The items laid out were very clear and well explained. The conversation around margin retention was good
column21: All of the goals were well articulated and clear. I do think the goals were all account focused and it would have been beneficial to hear what you Grant want to be better at or develop for yourself.
column23: The structure and content was well developed and explanations and impact clearly articulated. You are clearly knowledgeable and speak very confidently about each topic. Overall the flow felt a little rushed and I think some of the topics points would have benefitted from some time to breath in each section to provide space for impact to really sink in. It also would have presented as being more in control of the presentation.

column9: Renewal, scope and growth all well thought out. Great recap on the pricing and renewal strategy.
column11: Clearly described the value adds which supports the partnership and an equitable relationship!
column13: Nvidia is a people first customer, transparently sharing with them where they sit as a top provider is important … you’re doing that well.
column15: While you clearly have the ability to manage your customer I would like to understand the ROI on your innovations. You did well on outcomes, but would like more on lessons learned or results.
column17: Your transparency is refreshing and how you’ve overcome your challenges is appreciated. I like that the challenges pushed you to work cross functionally.
column21: I am 100% aligned with your goals
column23: You are a great communicator clear and logical in flow, with strong, confident, presentation skills. It’s always a pleasure to hear you present because of your knowledge of your accounts and passion.

column9: Clear narrative with a good focus.

column15: Partnering with our Ops team to think outside the box
column19: Strong plan with stretch goals. Looking forward to the 2026 roadmap updates.
column21: Clear, measurable, and forward thinking. All in line with a Sr. AD over an almost $4M/mo. account
column23: Led the discussion with confidence and presented well to executive leadership.

column19: Clear vision on continuing the path forward with Nvidia.
column21: This section ended up being a little constricted due to time. I did appreciate the focus on what you were working on but would have liked to see more on what you specifically are going to develop from a skills and growth standpoint.
column23: You very clearly own the account and speak from a place of practical knowledge. There was some excellent conversation on some of the topics which was great to see. The timing was slightly off after the first slide and cascaded to the rest of the slides. It would have been great to try and catch up at some point to help with the flow.

column19: Looking forward to implementation of the strong plan.

column23: Overall I found you to be informed and an expert on your account refreshing! You clearly communicated with a logical flow. Next go round pause for questions! However love the confidence.
